ities that appear 2-3 mm/yr lower\nthan the Quaternary rates. Over the 2015--2020 timespan, transient processes\nare also captured, notably on Mount Etna, showing both magmatic pressurization\nuplift and collapse of the eastern flank, but also all over Sicily where\nnumerous gravitational mass movements and anthropogenic ground subsidence are\ndetected.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 17 Aug 2022 09:42:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-08-18"}
